message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a method for detecting and classifying lung abnormalities in CT scans of cystic fibrosis patients using convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of medical imaging and analysis makes it relevant to the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of it being relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) sub-category.
